## Depth & Elevation (Cursor Shadow Philosophy)

Cursor uses dramatically large blur values with moderate opacity for diffused, atmospheric lift — cards feel like the page gently opened a space for them.

| Level | Treatment | Use |
|-------|-----------|-----|
| Flat (Level 0) | No shadow | Page background, text blocks |
| Border Ring (Level 1) | `rgba(38,37,30,0.1) 0 0 0 1px` | Standard card/container border — warm oklab |
| Border Medium (Level 1b) | `rgba(38,37,30,0.2) 0 0 0 1px` | Emphasized borders, active states |
| Ambient (Level 2) | `rgba(0,0,0,0.02) 0 0 16px, rgba(0,0,0,0.008) 0 0 8px` | Floating elements, subtle glow |
| Elevated Card (Level 3) | `rgba(0,0,0,0.14) 0 28px 70px, rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 14px 32px` | Modals, popovers, elevated cards |
| Focus | `rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 4px 12px` | Interactive focus feedback |

Dark theme shadows use same pattern with warm dark base:
- Border Ring: `rgba(242,241,237,0.06) 0 0 0 1px`
- Ambient: `rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 0 0 16px, rgba(0,0,0,0.15) 0 0 8px`
- Elevated: `rgba(0,0,0,0.5) 0 28px 70px, rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 0 14px 32px`

